    private IWarehouse _warehouse;

    public int getDaysToShip() {
        return _warehouse.getDaysToShip();
    }

    public void setWarehouse(IWarehouse warehouse) {
        _warehouse = warehouse;
    }
}

// PriorityOrder class with a delegate
class PriorityOrder extends Order {
    private IPriorityPlan _priorityPlan;

    @Override
    public int getDaysToShip() {
        return _priorityPlan.getDaysToShip();
    }

    public void setPriorityPlan(IPriorityPlan priorityPlan) {
        _priorityPlan = priorityPlan;
    }
}
```

**Explanation:**

* We define two interfaces, `IWarehouse` and `IPriorityPlan`, to represent the operations of the warehouse and priority plan, respectively.
* The `Order` class now has a private field `_warehouse` of type `IWarehouse`.
